parameters: This is "Taro's Home."

Today, he had planned to propose to his girlfriend,
"\C[27]Luna\C[0]," a true test of his manhood, at his house.

However, Taro was haunted by the fear that if he failed, it
might lead to a breakup.

\N<Taro>Sigh... I'm so nervous... The time we agreed on is almost
here...

\N<Taro>I've prepared everything for today, it should be fine... now
it's all up to Luna-chan...
\N<Taro>Sh-she's here...!

\N<Luna>Sorry to keep you waiting♪ Sorry, did I make you wait
long...?
\N<Taro>N-no, it's okay, I'm sorry for making you come all this way.
\N<Taro>It's not right to talk here, please come inside...
Runa_Normal_3_R
\N<Luna>O-okay...?? (Huh, he seems unusually nervous?)

\N<Luna>So... what's this important thing you wanted to talk about?
\N<Taro>We've been together for quite a while now, haven't we?
Runa_Normal_2_R

\N<Luna>Eh? Ahh~ Yeah, that's true. How long has it been since we
first met?
Runa_Smile_2_R

\N<Luna>Hehe, I was so surprised back then. I never thought I'd be
love-struck at first sight.

\N<Taro>That's because Luna-chan was so charming... I was more
surprised that you said yes right after I confessed.
Runa_Smile_1_R

\N<Luna>Because I thought Taro-kun was such a hardworking and
wonderful person...
\N<Taro>Luna-chan...

\N<Taro>I guess, even now and in the future... my feelings of loving
Luna-chan won't change.

\N<Luna>Why so sudden?... Ah, it's embarrassing.

\N<Taro>Actually, the reason I invited you over today is because
there's something I want to tell you...

\N<Taro>I want to be with Luna-chan forever and protect you for the
rest of my life, so, um... er... wi-will you...
Runa_Confuse_1_R
\N<Luna>...Yes?
\N<Taro>Will you... ma-ma-ma... marry
Just as he mustered all his courage to propose

\N<???>Hey Taro! You're there, right? I'm coming in~♪
\N<Taro>Wh-what the!?

\N<Taro>Huh?! Wh-who's there?!

\N<???>Oh man, nice place you got here. With a house like this, you
can surely pay back the \C[6]money\C[0], right?
Runa_Sad_2_R

\N<Taro>W-wait a minute! Who the hell are you guys? And what money
are you talking about...

\N<Debt Collector>Huh? You, man. Have you forgotten about the money you
borrowed?

\N<Debt Collector>You borrowed money from \C[31]Scam Company\C[0] saying it
was necessary for preparing to take on a high-level quest,
didn't ya?
Runa_Sad_1_R

\N<Taro>Th-that money should have been fully repaid already! With
the quest rewards...

\N<Debt Collector>Idiot! That was just the \C[6]principal\C[0]. You still got
\C[2]interest\C[0] to pay off. The interest of "\C[17]10
million gold\C[0]" that is!
Runa_Surprise_1_R
\C[17]\N<Luna>1...10 million gold\C[0]?!
\N<Taro>What?! What kind of outrageous interest is that?!
Runa_Sad_2_R

\N<Debt Collector>It was clearly written on the promissory note. Didn't you
read it? Look here, it's written "very~~~ small" at the
bottom, see?

\N<Taro>Th-that's... I wasn't told verbally, and I never imagined it
would be written in such tiny letters...

\N<Taro>Th-this is underhanded... making it hard to notice on
purpose and then demanding payment...
Runa_Sad_3_R
\N<Debt Collector>Stop your whining already, kid!

\N<Debt Collector>You're the one who signed the contract, Taro! Who do you
think you're talking to?!
\N<Taro>I-I'm sorry...

\N<Debt Collector>Do you even understand your position? It's useless to say
anything now if you can't even check a contract properly.

\N<Debt Collector>It's fine by me, though. If you refuse, I've got a nice girl
here... I'll just take her with me♪
Runa_Sad_2_R
\N<Taro>Wha...
\N<Debt Collector>Oh my❤ Taro's girl, she's got huge tits and a big ass♪

\N<Debt Collector>If I put her in a brothel, I could recover the debt♪ Hey
guys, take this girl away.
Runa_Surprise_1_R
\N<Luna>N-no!
Runa_Sad_4_R
\N<Taro>Wait! She has nothing to do with this!

The intention was to refuse the payment of the exorbitant
interest, but when she was taken hostage, Taro had no choice
but to accept the demands.
Runa_Sad_3_R

\N<Taro>Alright... I'll pay the interest... Just please, don't take
her away...
\N<Debt Collector>Huh, you said it? A man doesn't go back on his word.

\N<Debt Collector>As long as I get my money back, I don't care how. But you
probably can't think of a way to prepare such a large sum of
money, can you?
Runa_Sad_1_R
\N<Taro>...What should I do?

\N<Debt Collector>I'll introduce you to an island where you can make a
killing. There's a place to live, so earn there and send the
money.

\N<Debt Collector>For the sake of a woman, you'd risk your life hunting
monsters to prepare 10 million gold, wouldn't you? Easy,
right?

\N<Debt Collector>If you don't do it, I'll just take the girl... What will you
do?
Runa_Sad_5_R

\N<Luna>You don't have to ask! It's surely going to be dangerous
quests...
\N<Taro>...I will.
\N<Debt Collector>Huh? Speak up, can't hear you.
\N<Taro>I-I'll go to that island!!
Runa_Sad_2_R
\N<Luna>...Taro-kun...
Runa_Sad_1_R
\N<Debt Collector>Good♪... It's nice that you listen well.
\N<Debt Collector>Now that we've settled that... Here!
$Gold
$Gold
SmartPhone
\N<Taro>What's this...?
\N<Debt Collector>As you see, it's a \C[2]smartphone\C[0].

\N<Debt Collector>Use that smartphone to send the money you earn. It's a
system that makes it easy to transfer funds.

\N<Debt Collector>If you try to cheat, I'll know immediately, so don't do
anything unnecessary.
Runa_Sad_3_R
\N<Taro>...Understood.

\N<Debt Collector>The only way to the island is by boat, so I'll take you to
the port right after this... Start packing quickly.

\N<Debt Collector>Departure is in one hour. I'll be watching outside, so don't
get any funny ideas.
The debt collector left after saying his piece unilaterally.

Taro, who was supposed to become happy by proposing,
suddenly fell into a life of debt hell, and everything
before him turned pitch black.
Runa_Sad_1_R

\N<Luna>"Scam Company"... I've heard rumors about them demanding
ridiculous interest rates.

\N<Luna>You borrowed money... What did you use it for? I didn't know
about it.

\N<Taro>...Just like they said, it was for taking on a high-level
quest.

\C[14]\N<Taro>There was a reward item that I really wanted... It was my
first time borrowing money, so I had no idea how things
worked... I never imagined there would be such a trap,
damn...
Runa_Sad_3_R

\N<Luna>So that's what happened... We're adventurers, so I guess
these things happen, but still... That's terrible...
\N<Taro>(This is entirely my own doing...)

\N<Taro>(Damn it, instead of proposing, who would have thought it
would turn out like this...)

\N<Taro>(But regretting it won't solve anything, this is the only
way left...)

\N<Taro>That was scary earlier, I'm really sorry... for putting
Luna-chan through this... I'm not fit to be a lover.
Runa_Sad_1_R
\N<Luna>No, it's totally fine, I'm not worried about it.

\N<Taro>...As I said earlier, I have to go monster hunting on the
island now.

\N<Taro>Of course, I plan to earn 10 million G and return as soon as
possible.
\N<Taro>But as you know, monster hunting is a dangerous job.

\N<Taro>If something happens to me and I can't pay back the debt,
those debt collectors will take my girlfriend Luna-chan
away.
\N<Taro>Just imagining that scene is painful, worse than death.
\N<Taro>...So

\N<Taro>I think it's best to "\C[4]break up\C[0]" with Luna-chan
cleanly...

Taro made his decision with tears held back, out of concern
for Luna.
Runa_Surprise_1_R

\N<Luna>Wait, wait! Why does it have to come to that? Don't say such
sad things.
\N<Taro>But...

\N<Luna>Your problem is my problem too! Haven't we overcome many
hardships together until now?
Runa_Sad_2_R

\N<Luna>I'll "go with you" too, so let's pay off the debt quickly?
If we're together, we'll surely finish it soon.

\N<Luna>And once it's all paid off... can you "continue from
earlier" and tell me?
\N<Taro>Luna-chan...
